Project Many Doors

Trying to ideacraft a thing into existence. I came up with a concept of a game which is partly a life simulator where you have to work, take care of your body and your psyche and suffer consequences of sleeping badly. In the free time, you get to explore different stories in the form of jrpg's, and eventually witnessing the main character constructing their own, and in the background of this, you realize that the main character has deeply repressed trauma and your goal is to gradually get strong enough to integrate it, or to repress it even further, so a wacky mix of yume nikki, omori and its own flavor. 

